The paper focuses on developing a method for robots to identify and correct abnormal executions with the help of human attention transfer. This involves the use of neural networks for transferring attention from verbal reminders to robot visual perceiving. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves the use of AI techniques for reasoning and decision-making, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves human-robot interaction and the use of verbal reminders, which makes cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) a possible sub-category. The use of neural networks for attention transfer also makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of visual perception, which makes cs.CV (Computer Vision) a possible sub-category.
